PALLADIUM ATTRIBUTES (the 8 stats)

Rifts Earth uses the Palladium Books attribute system.  Every character has
eight core attributes rolled during character creation.

  IQ   Intelligence Quotient
       Affects skill percentages, number of skills, and some mental checks.
       Higher IQ gives a skill bonus and more secondary skills.

  ME   Mental Endurance
       Resistance to psionics, horror factor, and mental attacks.
       Affects saving throws vs. mind control and insanity.

  MA   Mental Affinity
       Charisma and force of personality.  Affects NPC reactions and
       the chance of trust/intimidation in social situations.

  PS   Physical Strength
       Raw muscle power.  Affects melee damage bonus and carrying capacity.
       PS 16+ adds a damage bonus; extraordinary PS (from bionics, RCC) uses
       different damage tables.

  PP   Physical Prowess
       Agility, coordination, and reflexes.  Affects to-hit bonus, combat
       initiative, and acrobatic skills.

  PE   Physical Endurance
       Stamina and constitution.  Affects HP bonus per level, saving throws
       vs. coma/death, and fatigue resistance.

  PB   Physical Beauty
       Physical attractiveness.  Affects NPC initial reactions.

  Spd  Speed
       Running speed in mph / meters per action.  Affects initiative and
       the ability to flee combat.

SECONDARY STATS (derived from the above)

  HP   Hit Points       (based on PE and level)
  SDC  Structural Damage Capacity  (based on race/OCC)
  MDC  Mega-Damage Capacity        (MDC beings only, replaces HP/SDC)
  PPE  Potential Psychic Energy    (magic pool)
  ISP  Inner Strength Points       (psionic pool)

